DESCRIPTION:The AGI Governance Fellowship is the inaugural three-week inten
 sive run by Johns Hopkins University's School of Government and Policy (SO
 GP) to develop the next generation of leaders in AI governance. COVERS: fr
 ontier AI legislation at state and federal levels\; building societal resi
 lience amid rapid capability growth\; democratic practices in AGI alignmen
 t\; and designing new governing institutions for the AGI era. WHO SHOULD A
 PPLY: early-career researchers and practitioners (within roughly eight yea
 rs of undergrad) with solid foundations in AI governance\, including congr
 essional staffers\, AGI company employees\, recent CS or policy PhDs\, and
