UID:horizon-fellowship-2027-cohort@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T115027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260830
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260831
SUMMARY:Deadline: Horizon Fellowship\, 2027 Cohort
DESCRIPTION:The Horizon Fellowship places technologists\, scientists and re
 searchers with emerging-technology expertise into US federal agencies\, co
 ngressional offices and Washington DC think tanks to work on AI\, biotechn
 ology and emerging-technology policy. The 2027 cohort runs three tiers: ju
 nior fellows (under three years of experience\, no PhD) at a USD 78\,000 b
 ase for six months\; fellows (three or more years of relevant experience\,
  or a PhD) at USD 130\,000 for twelve months\; and a newly added senior fe
 llow tier (twelve or more years of experience with a leadership background
 ) at USD 190\,000 or more for twelve months. All tiers receive a USD 17\,0
 00 benefits stipend\, a USD 3\,000 professional development stipend and up
  to USD 3\,000 in relocation assistance\, and all are potentially renewabl
 e. The programme year begins with part-time remote training from January t
 o March 2027\, followed by matching in April and May and placement from sp
 ring or summer 2027 onward. Most offers are expected by the end of Novembe
 r 2026. ELIGIBILITY: no prior policy experience or specific degree is requ
 ired\, and Horizon explicitly welcomes candidates from diverse backgrounds
 \; fellows must reside in Washington DC for the placement\, and non-citize
 ns need work authorisation that does not depend on sponsorship. Applicatio
 ns close 30 August 2026 at 11:59pm Anywhere on Earth.\n\nOrganisation: Hor
 izon Institute for Public Service\nLocation: Washington DC\, USA (residenc
 e required for placement). Part-time remote training January to March 2027
 .\nAward: Base salary of USD 78\,000 for junior fellows\, USD 130\,000 for
  fellows\, and USD 190\,000 or more for senior fellows\, plus a USD 17\,00
 0 benefits stipend\, a USD 3\,000 professional development stipend\, and u
 p to USD 3\,000 relocation assistance. No application fee.\nDuration: 6 mo
 nths for junior fellows\, 12 months for fellows and senior fellows\, with 
 potential renewal. Part-time remote training January to March 2027\, match
 ing April to May 2027\, placement from summer 2027.\n\nMore: https://horiz
 onpublicservice.org/applications-open-for-2027-horizon-fellowship-cohort/?
 utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://horizonpublicservice.org/applications-open-for-2027-horizon-fel
 lowship-cohort/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Washington DC\, USA (residence required for placement). Part-time 
 remote training January to March 2027.
END:VEVENT
